<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING PUMPS LUK VT73 AND LF93 - MAINTENANCE - STARTUP</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
        <title>STARTUP</title>
        <para>With a minimum drive speed of 600 rpm, a pump should prime almost immediately if provision is made to
            initially purge air from the system. Failure to prime within a reasonable length of time may result in
            damage due to lack of lubrication. Inlet lines must be tight and free from air leaks; however, it may be
            necessary to crack a fitting on the outlet side of the pump to purge entrapped air.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
